project: Event Sheet Opening and End Game

When the last wolf falls under Kaito's katana, the silence that follows is almost palpable. That red giant finally collapses on the ground of the central square. Its form begins to dissolve into a silvery mist that slowly disappears into the morning air.

As the last drop of this mist disperses, the first lights of dawn begin to shine behind the mountains. The rays of sunlight, initially soft and pink, gain intensity, gradually bathing the village in golden tones. The lanterns that still trembled in the night wind begin to lose their brightness, becoming redundant in the face of the growing light.

The villages, which had sheltered fearfully in their homes, begin to emerge timidly. They find their streets clean, without any trace of the terrible wolves that inspired so much fear. In the center of the square, Kaito remains standing, his katana still raised, watching the sunrise that paints the sky in shades of coral and amber.
Event Sheet Opening and End Game

One night, under the heavy silence of the mountains, the small village of Akakawa lies in an unsettling darkness. The lanterns that normally illuminate the streets now tremble violently in the wind, casting dancing shadows on the walls of the houses.

In the highest house in the village, a samurai named Kaito wakes to the distant howling of wolves. His instincts trigger a silent alarm in his heart.

As he stands up, the sound repeats, this time closer. Kaito can feel the ground vibrating beneath his bare feet. He knows that normal wolves would never approach an inhabited village so boldly.

As he opens the door to his house, he is greeted by a sight that makes his blood run cold. Huge wolves, with eyes that glow like hot coals, roam the streets of the village. The leader of the pack, a gigantic wolf with red fur, stands in the center of the main square.

With a deep sigh, Kaito descends the steps of his house with his bow. He knows this will be a long and dangerous night, but he is prepared to defend Akakawa with his last breath. The wind blows hard again, and the wolves turn in unison to face the samurai...
